<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="description" content="Example page showing important head elements">
  <meta name="author" content="Student">
  <base href="https://example.com/">
  <link rel="icon" href="favicon.ico">
  <title>All Important Head Elements</title>

  <!-- style and script can be empty as requested -->
  <style>
    /* Empty style block - placeholder for future CSS */
  </style>

  <script>
    // Empty script block - placeholder for future JavaScript
  </script>

  <!-- Comments: 
       <title> sets the page title shown in browser/tab.
       <meta charset> defines character encoding.
       <meta name="description"> provides a short description for search engines.
       <meta name="author"> indicates the page author.
       <base> sets the base URL for relative links on the page.
       <link> can reference external resources (favicon, stylesheets).
       <style> contains internal CSS.
       <script> contains JS.
  -->
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Head Elements Demonstration</h1>
  <p>This page includes title, meta tags, base, link, style, and script elements with comments explaining their purpose.</p>
</body>
</html>
